Articles.Content:
If you are somewhat stuck still using 1.1.2, give this a try. Your description is different, but perhaps this might help. Download this, unzip it, and put the contents into your GameData directory. (It's small, just a couple Kb.)

https://www.dropbox.com/s/gyyaavynxkwtxhg/EditorCPUFix v00.02.zip?dl=0

Additionally, what might help better is if we can get the other log (output_log.txt). That usually give a bit more info about what's happening before and up to the crash.

Thank you for replying.

So I downloaded this and placed the contents in GameData. I went to VAB and made something real quick, and when I tried to launch the game crashed. And now it does that even without the fix you gave me (usually loads the craft and crashes in flight or if I cycle through the kerbals)
